<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="82" pageId="6" pageNumber="81" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1518,2012]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,151,321]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="82" pageId="6" pageNumber="81">
The checklist contains 73 presently known species of 
<taxonomicName box="[763,866,1518,1544]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Gobiidae</taxonomicName>
in the Mediterranean Sea (
<tableCitation box="[1173,1258,1518,1544]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,239,765,789]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="TABLE 1. The checklist of the species of gobies (Gobiidae) confirmed in the Mediterranean Sea. Abbrevations of the fish" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF18A9E6D417667AFF02FD4814B51269" pageId="6" pageNumber="81" tableUuid="DF18A9E6D417667AFF02FD4814B51269">Table 1</tableCitation>
). All species in the list have their presence verified by the criteria in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Lipej, L. &amp; Dulcic, J." box="[757,1000,1554,1581]" pageId="6" pageNumber="81" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref17284" refString="Kovacic, M., Lipej, L. &amp; Dulcic, J. (2020) Evidence approach to checklists: critical revision of the checklist of the Adriatic Sea fishes. Zootaxa, 4767 (1), 1 - 55." type="journal article" year="2020">
Kovačić 
<emphasis box="[859,910,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="81">et al</emphasis>
. (2020)
</bibRefCitation>
i.e. by at least one specimen from the Mediterranean stored in a public collection or by a diagnosis that positively identifies the species from the photo or from the description in a publication (
<tableCitation box="[609,693,1626,1652]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,239,765,789]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="TABLE 1. The checklist of the species of gobies (Gobiidae) confirmed in the Mediterranean Sea. Abbrevations of the fish" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF18A9E6D417667AFF02FD4814B51269" pageId="6" pageNumber="81" tableUuid="DF18A9E6D417667AFF02FD4814B51269">Table 1</tableCitation>
). Two species were described apparently based on Mediterranean material with 
<typeStatus box="[312,360,1663,1689]" pageId="6" pageNumber="81">type</typeStatus>
material lost and no published evidence of other Mediterranean material in public collection, so the diagnostic characters in the original description are the only evidence (
<tableCitation box="[1042,1128,1698,1724]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,239,765,789]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="TABLE 1. The checklist of the species of gobies (Gobiidae) confirmed in the Mediterranean Sea. Abbrevations of the fish" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF18A9E6D417667AFF02FD4814B51269" pageId="6" pageNumber="81" tableUuid="DF18A9E6D417667AFF02FD4814B51269">Table 1</tableCitation>
). All other records, except 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ruppell 1830)" baseAuthorityName="Ruppell" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[151,708,1734,1760]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Cryptocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caeruleopunctatus">
<emphasis box="[151,527,1734,1760]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="81">Cryptocentrus caeruleopunctatus</emphasis>
(Rüppell 1830)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Valenciennes, 1837)" baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[766,1244,1734,1760]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Aulopareia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="unicolor">
<emphasis box="[766,995,1734,1760]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="81">Aulopareia unicolor</emphasis>
(Valenciennes, 1837)
</taxonomicName>
, were confirmed in the Mediterranean by at least one specimen from the Mediterranean stored in public collection having the related published reference. The Mediterranean record of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ruppell" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[707,945,1806,1832]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Cryptocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caeruleopunctatus">
<emphasis box="[707,945,1806,1832]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="81">C. caeruleopunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was verified by the diagnosis that positively identify species from the photo. Two more records of alien gobies in the Mediterranean Sea are problematic as they lack diagnostic characters for positive identification in the described morphology in their first record publications: 
<taxonomicName authority="in Akel &amp; Samir (2017)" authorityName="in Akel &amp; Samir" authorityYear="2017" box="[151,559,1914,1940]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Aulopareia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="unicolor">
<emphasis box="[151,279,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="81">A. unicolor</emphasis>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Akel, E. S. H. K. H. &amp; Samir, I. R." box="[316,559,1914,1940]" pageId="6" pageNumber="81" pagination="63 - 66" refId="ref15553" refString="Akel, E. S. H. K. H. &amp; Samir, I. R. (2017) A first record of Aulopareia unicolor (Valenciennes, 1837) (Family: Gobiidae) in the Mediterranean Sea, Egypt. Egyptian Journal of Aquatic Biology &amp; Fisheries, 21 (2), 63 - 66. https: // doi. org / 10.21608 / ejabf. 2017.3533" type="journal article" year="2017">Akel &amp; Samir (2017)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Cuvier &amp; Valenciennes, 1837) in Akel (2017)" authorityName="in Akel" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Cuvier &amp; Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[616,1432,1914,1940]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Bathygobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cyclopterus">
<emphasis box="[616,894,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="81">Bathygobius cyclopterus</emphasis>
(Cuvier &amp; Valenciennes, 1837) in Akel (2017)
</taxonomicName>
. However, the identity of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Akel &amp; Samir" authorityYear="2017" box="[436,563,1950,1976]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Aulopareia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="unicolor">
<emphasis box="[436,563,1950,1976]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="81">A. unicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was verified by Helen Larson (personal communication) using the diagnosis that positively identified the species from the published photo in 
<bibRefCitation author="Akel, E. S. H. K. H. &amp; Samir, I. R." box="[881,1123,1986,2012]" pageId="6" pageNumber="81" pagination="63 - 66" refId="ref15553" refString="Akel, E. S. H. K. H. &amp; Samir, I. R. (2017) A first record of Aulopareia unicolor (Valenciennes, 1837) (Family: Gobiidae) in the Mediterranean Sea, Egypt. Egyptian Journal of Aquatic Biology &amp; Fisheries, 21 (2), 63 - 66. https: // doi. org / 10.21608 / ejabf. 2017.3533" type="journal article" year="2017">Akel &amp; Samir (2017)</bibRefCitation>
, and it is therefore included in the checklist. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Akel" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Cuvier &amp; Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[333,609,151,177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Bathygobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cyclopterus">
<emphasis box="[333,609,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Bathygobius cyclopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been rejected from the present checklist because its identity and provenance could not be verified. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pallas 1814)" baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[478,933,187,213]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Proterorhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marmoratus">
<emphasis box="[478,777,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Proterorhinus marmoratus</emphasis>
(Pallas 1814)
</taxonomicName>
, listed as a Mediterranean species in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Patzner, R. A." pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="177 - 206" refId="ref17018" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Patzner, R. A. (2011) North-Eastern Atlantic and Mediterranean gobies. In: Patzner, R. A., Van Tassell, J. L., Kovacic, M. &amp; Kapoor, B. G. (Eds.), The biology of gobies. Science Publishers, CRC Press, Taylor &amp; Francis Group, New York, New York, pp. 177 - 206. https: // doi. org / 10.1201 / b 11397 - 15" type="book chapter" year="2011">Kovačić &amp; Patzner (2011)</bibRefCitation>
, was also excluded from the present list since all references to the presence of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[1206,1369,223,248]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Proterorhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marmoratus">
<emphasis box="[1206,1369,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">P. marmoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the marine conditions of the northeast Mediterranean areas (summarised in 
<bibRefCitation author="Papaconstantinou, C." box="[944,1205,259,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" refId="ref18329" refString="Papaconstantinou, C. (2014) Fauna Graeciae. An updated checklist of the fishes in the Hellenic seas. Monagraphs on Marine Sciences 7. National Centre for Marine Research, Athens, 338 pp." type="book" year="2014">Papaconstantinou 2014</bibRefCitation>
) are without original data, and none of them satisfies any of the criteria for the verified presence (
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Lipej, L. &amp; Dulcic, J." box="[1004,1230,295,321]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref17284" refString="Kovacic, M., Lipej, L. &amp; Dulcic, J. (2020) Evidence approach to checklists: critical revision of the checklist of the Adriatic Sea fishes. Zootaxa, 4767 (1), 1 - 55." type="journal article" year="2020">
Kovačić 
<emphasis box="[1106,1155,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
